                            <comment id="14455410" author="ryanhennig" created="Wed, 29 Aug 2012 18:27:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is fixed in 2.12.1 and later&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15032653" author="mbatra" created="Mon, 30 Nov 2015 22:51:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We recently upgraded to version 2.19 from version 2.18.1 and are seeing the error with non zero exit code.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15034840" author="tibor17" created="Tue, 1 Dec 2015 23:25:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mbatra&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mbatra&quot;&gt;mbatra&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Is the root cause identical with  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1197&quot; title=&quot;Surefire 2.19 breaks tests under Windows due to fork problem&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SUREFIRE-1197&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SUREFIRE-1197&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15034943" author="mbatra" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2015 00:17:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes we are having the same issue as described in surefire-1197. In our case, it&apos;s happening on Linux server.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15035495" author="tibor17" created="Wed, 2 Dec 2015 09:01:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It will be fixed in 2.19.1. It will require you to use some system property.&lt;br/&gt;
The thing is that surefire cannot wait infinitely for the sub-process to&lt;br/&gt;
die. Since we don&apos;t know how long your code is going to prolong the&lt;br/&gt;
shutdown hook life time we employ the timeout and you will be able to&lt;br/&gt;
modify the timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

</comment>
